hellenic Socialist Movement|PASOK]]<br>{{Percentage bar|4.44|c=green}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Election 2015 September|url=http://ekloges.ypes.gr/current/v/public/index.html|publisher=Ministry of Interior|accessdate=26 September 2015}}</ref>\n|}\n|}\n\n==Members of Parliament==\n\n===Current members===\n*[[Theodoros Dritsas]] ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Costas Douzinas]]  ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Georgia Gennia]]  ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Eleni Stamataki]]  ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Konstantinos Katsafados]] ''[[New Democracy (Greece)|ND]]''\n*[[Nikos Kouzilos]] ''[[Golden Dawn (Greece)|XA]]''\n\n=== Members of Parliament (Jan 2015 - Sep 2015)===\n*[[Theodoros Dritsas]] ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Stathis Leoutsakos]] ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Eleni Stamataki]] ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Konstantinos Katsafados]] ''[[New Democracy (Greece)|ND]]''\n*[[Stavroula Antonakou]] ''[[The River (Greece)|The River]]\n*[[Nikos Kouzilos]] ''[[Golden Dawn (Greece)|XA]]''\n\n===Members of Parliament (2012\u201315)===\n*[[Konstantinos Arvanitopoulos]] ''[[New Democracy (Greece)|ND]]''\n*[[Konstantinos Katsafados]] ''[[New Democracy (Greece)|ND]]''\n*[[Thodoris Dritsas]] ''[[SYRIZA]]''\n*[[Panagiotis Melas]] ''[[ANEL]]''\n*[[Nikolaos Kouzilos]] ''[[Golden Dawn (Greece)|XA]]''\n*[[Repousi Maria]] ''[[DIMAR]]''\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Greek parliament constituencies}}\n\n[[Category:Parliamentary constituencies of Greece]]\n[[Category:1958 establishments in Greece]]\n[[Category:Constituencies established in 1958]]\n[[Category:Piraeus]]\n\n\n{{Greece-poli-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WOSlinker", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix bold", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Piraeus_A"}
{"title_page": "Elisabethszell", "text_new": "{{Infobox Ortsteil einer Gemeinde in Deutschland\n| Art = Ortsteil               \n| Municipality           = [[Haibach, Lower Bavaria|Haibach]]\n| district               = Straubing-Bogen\n|coordinates       = {{coord|49.027|12.7501|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| Bundesland             = Bavaria\n| H\u00f6he                   = 632\n| Fl\u00e4che                 =\n| Einwohner              = 292\n| Stand                  = 1987-05-25<ref>[http://wiki-de.genealogy.net/GOV:ELIELL_W8441 wiki-de.genealogy.net]{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| Eingemeindungsdatum    = <!-- 1978-1-1 -->\n| PLZ                    = 94353\n| Vorwahl                = 09963, 09965\n| Lagekarte              =\n| Lagekarte-Beschreibung =\n| image_photo            = Elisabethszell.jpg\n| image_caption          = Elisabethszell\n}}\n\n'''Elisabethszell''' is a parish village (''Pfarrdorf'') in the municipality of [[Haibach, Lower Bavaria|Haibach]] in the [[Lower Bavaria]]n county of [[Straubing-Bogen]] in [[Germany]].\n\n== History ==\nIn 1346 in the place then known as Atzenzell, which belonged to the parish (''Pfarrei'') of Haselbach, a priory of [[Oberalteich Abbey|Benedictine abbey of Oberalteich]] was established. It existed, with interruptions, until  church land in Bavaria was seized in 1803.\n\nIn 1498 the [[Benedictines]] were driven out by the Paulsdorfs at [[Falkenfels Castle]]. It was the Countess of Schwarzenberg, whose had inherited Elisabethszell from her forebears, who allowed Oberalteich Abbey to buy back the priory estates for a moderate sum in 1621, whereupon the clergy returned to Elisabethszell.\n\nSecularisation in Bavaria in 1803 spelt the end of the priory at Elisabethszell. In 1805, Elisabethszell, hitherto part of the parish of [[Haselbach (Niederbayern)|Haselbach]], became an independent parish. The priory was given by the state to the municipality of Elisabethszell for the establishment of a school. On 11 July 1877 the newly built parish church was consecrated by Bishop [[Ignatius von Senestr\u00e9y]].\n\nThe old cemetery was closed in 1967 and turned into a car park in the 1970s. A new cemetery was created above the Pfarrhof. With municipal reforms in Bavaria, the former municipality of Elisabethszell lost its independence and was incorporated on 1 January 1978 into Haibach.\n\n\n=== Population growth ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe6\"\n! Jahr\n! <small>1840</small><ref name=\"HistGV52\"/>\n! <small>1867</small><ref name=\"GVZ1867\"/>\n! <small>1871</small>\n! <small>1885</small>\n! <small>1900</small>\n! <small>1925</small>\n! <small>1950</small>\n! <small>1961</small>\n! <small>1970</small>\n! <small>1987</small>\n|-\n|Population of the ''Pfarrdorf'' of Elisabethszell<ref>[http://wiki-de.genealogy.net/GOV:ELIELL_W8441 Einwohnerentwicklung Elisabethszell]{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} auf gov.genealogy.net</ref>\n|\n|\n|220\n|242\n|255\n|230\n|289\n|227\n|264\n|292\n|-\n|Population of the municipality of Elisabethszell\n|745\n|776\n|776\n|825\n|821\n|840\n|906\n|774\n|745\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== Sights ==\n* Parish church of St. Elisabeth. It was built from 1834 to 1837 to replace a demolished predecessor church. The church furnishings were completed between 1870 and 1875.\n\n== Societies ==\n* Elisabethszell Volunteer Fire Service (''Freiwillige Feuerwehr Elisabethszell''), founded in 1878.\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commonscat}}\n* [http://bavarica.digitale-sammlungen.de/de/fs1/object/display/bsb10334148_00005.html?context Monumenta Elisabetcellensia]\n* [http://www.haibach-elisabethszell.de/start_gemeinde.htm Website der Gemeinde Haibach-Elisabethszell]Ortsdatenbank\n* {{BLO Ortsdatenbank|objekt=Elisabethszell|val=25298}}\n\n== References ==\n<references>\n<ref name=\"GVZ1867\">\n{{citation|title=Verzeichni\u00df der Gemeinden des K\u00f6nigreichs Bayern nach dem Stande der Bev\u00f6lkerung im Dezember 1867 : mit ...: mit Ausscheidung nach Familien, Geschlecht und Religionsverh\u00e4ltnissen, geordnet nach Kreisen, Verwaltungs-Disctricten und Gerichtssprengeln, unter Beif\u00fcgung der einschl\u00e4gigen, Rent\u00e4mter, Forst\u00e4mter, Baubeh\u00f6rden Notariatssitze und Advokatenstellen, sowie der Zahl der zu den Gemeinden geh\u00f6rigen Ortschaften, nebst alphabetischem Index|publisher=Ackermann|publication-place=M\u00fcnchen|pages=52-53|date=1869|language=German|url=http://bavarica.digitale-sammlungen.de/de/fs1/object/display/bsb10316430_00064.html|access-date= 2015-01-02\n}}, Format: Digitalisat</ref>\n<ref name=\"HistGV52\">\n{{citation|periodical=Beitr\u00e4ge zur Statistik Bayerns|title=Bayern 1840-1952: Historisches Gemeindeverzeichnis: Die Einwohnerzahlen der Gemeinden Bayerns in der Zeit von 1840 bis 1952|volume=Heft 192|publication-place=M\u00fcnchen|page=52|date=1953|language=German|url=http://daten.digitale-sammlungen.de/bsb00066439/image_63\n}}, Format: digitalised</ref>\n</references>\n\n[[Category:Straubing-Bogen]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Ortsteil einer Gemeinde in Deutschland\n| Art = Ortsteil               \n| Municipality           = [[Haibach, Lower Bavaria|Haibach]]\n| district               = Straubing-Bogen\n| Alternativanzeige-Gemeindename = Haibach\n|coordinates       = {{coord|49.027|12.7501|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| Bundesland             = Bavaria\n| H\u00f6he                   = 632\n| H\u00f6he-Bezug             = DE-NN\n| Fl\u00e4che                 =\n| Einwohner              = 292\n| Stand                  = 1987-05-25\n| Einwohner-Quelle       = <ref>[http://wiki-de.genealogy.net/GOV:ELIELL_W8441 wiki-de.genealogy.net]{{Dead link|date=August 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| Eingemeindungsdatum    = 1978-1-1\n| PLZ                    = 94353\n| Postleitzahl2          =\n| Vorwahl                = 09963, 09965\n| Lagekarte              =\n| Lagekarte-Beschreibung =\n| Poskarte               = Deutschland Bayern\n| image_photo            = Elisabethszell.jpg\n| image_caption          = Elisabethszell\n}}\n\n'''Elisabethszell''' is a parish village (''Pfarrdorf'') in the municipality of [[Haibach, Lower Bavaria|Haibach]] in the [[Lower Bavaria]]n county of [[Straubing-Bogen]] in [[Germany]].\n\n== History ==\nIn 1346 in the place then known as Atzenzell, which belonged to the parish (''Pfarrei'') of Haselbach, a priory of [[Oberalteich Abbey|Benedictine abbey of Oberalteich]] was established. It existed, with interruptions, until  church land in Bavaria was seized in 1803.\n\nIn 1498 the [[Benedictines]] were driven out by the Paulsdorfs at [[Falkenfels Castle]]. It was the Countess of Schwarzenberg, whose had inherited Elisabethszell from her forebears, who allowed Oberalteich Abbey to buy back the priory estates for a moderate sum in 1621, whereupon the clergy returned to Elisabethszell.\n\nSecularisation in Bavaria in 1803 spelt the end of the priory at Elisabethszell. In 1805, Elisabethszell, hitherto part of the parish of [[Haselbach (Niederbayern)|Haselbach]], became an independent parish. The priory was given by the state to the municipality of Elisabethszell for the establishment of a school. On 11 July 1877 the newly built parish church was consecrated by Bishop [[Ignatius von Senestr\u00e9y]].\n\nThe old cemetery was closed in 1967 and turned into a car park in the 1970s. A new cemetery was created above the Pfarrhof. With municipal reforms in Bavaria, the former municipality of Elisabethszell lost its independence and was incorporated on 1 January 1978 into Haibach.\n\n\n=== Population growth ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- class=\"hintergrundfarbe6\"\n! Jahr\n! <small>1840</small><ref name=\"HistGV52\"/>\n! <small>1867</small><ref name=\"GVZ1867\"/>\n! <small>1871</small>\n! <small>1885</small>\n! <small>1900</small>\n! <small>1925</small>\n! <small>1950</small>\n! <small>1961</small>\n! <small>1970</